defaultWritten evidence from the UK Major Ports Group (WRT 009)defaultSummarydefault1
default              
defaultThe arrangements for winter resilience for transport have improved greatly since the winter of 2009/10. The strategic importance of ports to the UK economy is now much better recognised in planning arrangements. Moreover much of the strategic stockpile of 
defaultsalt and grit is being stored at ports which can provide the necessary space, access to supply lines, and handling and distribution expertise. It is essential that ports and main connecting road and rail links continue to be given priority in winter resili
defaultence planning. 
defaultIntroductiondefault2
default              
defaultUKMPG is one of two associations representing ports in the UK.  Our 9 member groups handle over 70 percent of the UK’s international trade by volume, and therefore play a significant role in supporting the UK economy and prom
defaultoting exports.  UK ports are privately financed and do not seek any financial help from the taxpayer.  
