defaultther including snow and flooding, and carrying out regular test exercises.
defaultCurrent positiondefault&#xa0;default8
default              
defaultMajor ports are satisfied that prioritization and planning arrangements are now much improved since the problems encountered in winter 2009/10. Should there be a
default recurrence of severe wintery conditions in winter 2013/4, ports will work closely with customers, stakeholders and other infrastructure providers to ensure that any disruption is kept to a minimum. It is essential that connecting infrastructure to and fro
defaultm ports receives priority for snow and ice clearance etc – ports are liaising closely with h
defaultighway authorities and Network R
defaultail on this. It also remains important that ports have guaranteed salt and grit availability in the event of severe weather. 
